## Lombok in Spring Boot

---

### рџ§  Why Lombok?

Every Java class needs boilerplate code that adds **zero business value**:

```java
// Without Lombok вЂ” you write ALL of this manually
public class Student {
    private String name;
    private int age;

    public Student() {}
    public Student(String name, int age) { ... }

    public String getName() { return name; }
    public void setName(String name) { this.name = name; }
    public int getAge() { return age; }
    public void setAge(int age) { this.age = age; }

    @Override
    public String toString() { ... }

    @Override
    public boolean equals(Object o) { ... }

    @Override
    public int hashCode() { ... }
}
```

**Lombok generates all of this at compile time** via annotations. Your actual source file becomes:

```java
// With Lombok вЂ” clean!
@Data
@AllArgsConstructor
@NoArgsConstructor
public class Student {
    private String name;
    private int age;
}
```

