### рџ“Њ All Key Annotations

---

#### 1пёЏвѓЈ `@Getter` / `@Setter`

```java
@Getter
@Setter
public class Student {
    private String name;
    private int age;
}

// Lombok generates:
// getName(), setName()
// getAge(),  setAge()
```

Can also apply to individual fields:

```java
public class Student {
    @Getter @Setter
    private String name;

    @Getter                  // only getter, no setter
    private int age;
}
```

---

#### 2пёЏвѓЈ `@NoArgsConstructor` / `@AllArgsConstructor` / `@RequiredArgsConstructor`

```java
@NoArgsConstructor       // public Student() {}
@AllArgsConstructor      // public Student(String name, int age) {}
public class Student {
    private String name;
    private int age;
}
```

```java
// @RequiredArgsConstructor вЂ” only for final or @NonNull fields
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class Student {
    private final String name;    // included in constructor
    private final Address address;// included in constructor
    private int age;              // NOT included (not final)
}
// generates: public Student(String name, Address address) {}
```

> `@RequiredArgsConstructor` is the **Spring Boot DI standard** вЂ” pairs perfectly with constructor injection.

---

#### 3пёЏвѓЈ `@ToString`

```java
@ToString
public class Student {
    private String name;
    private int age;
}
// generates:
// Student(name=Nivas, age=21)

// Exclude a field:
@ToString(exclude = "password")
public class User {
    private String username;
    private String password;
}
```

---

#### 4пёЏвѓЈ `@EqualsAndHashCode`

```java
@EqualsAndHashCode
public class Student {
    private String name;
    private int age;
}
// generates equals() and hashCode() based on all fields

// Use only specific fields:
@EqualsAndHashCode(of = {"name"})
```

---

#### 5пёЏвѓЈ `@Data` вЂ” The All-in-One

```java
@Data
public class Student {
    private String name;
    private int age;
}
```

`@Data` = `@Getter` + `@Setter` + `@ToString` + `@EqualsAndHashCode` + `@RequiredArgsConstructor`

> Most commonly used for **DTOs and Entity classes**.

---

#### 6пёЏвѓЈ `@Builder` вЂ” Builder Pattern

```java
@Builder
@Data
public class Student {
    private String name;
    private int age;
    private String email;
    private Address address;
}

// Usage вЂ” no need to remember constructor order
Student s = Student.builder()
    .name("Nivas")
    .age(21)
    .email("nivas@gmail.com")
    .build();
```

> Perfect when a class has **many fields** вЂ” much cleaner than a long constructor call.

---

#### 7пёЏвѓЈ `@Slf4j` вЂ” Logging (very useful in Spring Boot)

```java
@Slf4j
@Service
public class StudentService {

    public void process() {
        log.info("Processing student...");
        log.debug("Debug info here");
        log.error("Something went wrong");
    }
}
// No need to write:
// private static final Logger log = LoggerFactory.getLogger(StudentService.class);
```

---

#### 8пёЏвѓЈ `@Value` (Lombok) вЂ” Immutable class

```java
@Value   // all fields final, no setters, all-args constructor
public class StudentDTO {
    String name;
    int age;
}
// Use for immutable response/request objects
```

