### рџ“Љ Quick Reference Card

| Annotation | Generates |
|---|---|
| `@Getter` | `getXxx()` for all fields |
| `@Setter` | `setXxx()` for all fields |
| `@NoArgsConstructor` | `ClassName() {}` |
| `@AllArgsConstructor` | Constructor with all fields |
| `@RequiredArgsConstructor` | Constructor for `final` / `@NonNull` fields |
| `@ToString` | `toString()` |
| `@EqualsAndHashCode` | `equals()` + `hashCode()` |
| `@Data` | All of the above combined |
| `@Builder` | Builder pattern |
| `@Slf4j` | `log` object for logging |
| `@Value` | Immutable class (all final) |

---

### рџ”‘ Interview One-Liner
> "Lombok is a compile-time annotation processor that eliminates Java boilerplate вЂ” getters, setters, constructors, toString вЂ” keeping code clean. In Spring Boot, `@RequiredArgsConstructor` + `final` fields is the standard pattern for constructor injection without writing any constructor manually."
